# Organize UI Rules

## Code Organization Principles
- Keep components in logical groupings
- Separate UI components from business logic
- Use consistent naming conventions
- Remove unused imports and dependencies

## File Structure Rules
```
client/
├── components/
│   ├── ui/           # Reusable UI components
│   └── ...           # Feature-specific components
├── hooks/            # Custom React hooks
├── lib/              # Utility functions
└── pages/            # Page components
```

## Component Guidelines
- Each component should have a single responsibility
- Use TypeScript for type safety
- Follow React best practices
- Include proper prop validation
- Export components with meaningful names

## Dependencies Management
- Remove unused dependencies from package.json
- Keep dev dependencies separate from runtime dependencies
- Use exact versions for critical dependencies
- Regularly audit and update dependencies

## Code Quality Rules
- Use consistent code formatting (Prettier)
- Follow ESLint rules
- Write meaningful commit messages
- Include documentation for complex components
- Use meaningful variable and function names

## Performance Considerations
- Optimize bundle size by removing unused code
- Use React.memo for expensive components
- Implement proper error boundaries
- Lazy load components when appropriate
